Attachments

-NCMEC Cybertip #161508488

 

Narrative

On 5/22/23, the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Section /Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force received NCMEC CyberTip # 161508488. The Cyber Tip, generated by Tiktok, indicated that a subject uploaded child pornography to the internet. The CyberTip was assigned to TFC Cooke for investigation.

 

The CyberTip provided the following information pertaining to the suspect:

 

Address: US
Email Address: gotbunk@gmail.com
Screen/User Name: itsyo_boyyya
IP Address: 24.154.92.77 (Login)
04-30-2023 01:45:39 UTC

 

The CyberTip contained 2 reported child pornography files. TFC Cooke reviewed the reported child pornography files and determined that both files constitute child pornography as it is defined under Maryland law. These files are described below:

 

Filename: 72290205847165530061615084880.mp4

Description: 15 second video of a fully nude white male, reasonably believed to be 10 -12 years of age, masturbating his erect penis. The male is underdeveloped and devoid of pubic hair.

 

Filename: 72290205847165530061615084881.mp4

Description: 15 second video of a fully nude white male, reasonably believed to be 10 -12 years of age, masturbating his erect penis. The male is underdeveloped and devoid of pubic hair.

 

 

The CyberTip indicated that the following IP address 24.154.92.77 (03-11-2023 16:58:51 UTC) was utilized to upload the reported contraband files.

 

TFC Cooke conducted a query of the upload IP address through an open-source database and determined that it is registered through Armstrong Cable and geo-locates generally to the Port Deposit area of Cecil County, Maryland.

TFC Cooke conducted a query of the suspect email address through an open-source database and determined that it was being used by a "Noel McDonald." Further queries through law-enforcement databases determined that "Noel McDonald" resided at  11 NORTH FRIENDSHIP COURT, COLORA MD 21917. A query of this address returned contact information for "Noel McDonald's" father, Robert Glenn McDonald. McDonald was contacted and confirmed his son's identity and ownership of the suspect Tiktok account / email account. McDonald was provided an internet safety talk and advised that he would speak with Noel regarding the incident.

 

Case Status

Closed by exception.
